1. GET /products
✅ Check all available products
➡️ Test status 200

2. POST /orders
✅ Place new order
Body (JSON):

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "productId": 2,
  "quantity": 3,
  "status": "placed"
}
➡️ Test response has correct fields

3. PATCH /orders/1
✅ Update order status
Body:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "status": "shipped"
}
➡️ Test status updated to shipped

4. DELETE /orders/1
✅ Delete order
➡️ Status 200 + response empty

🧪 Step 4: Add Postman Test Scripts
Example for GET /products:

js
Copy
Edit
pm.test("Status code is 200", function () {
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

pm.test("Response has array of products", function () {
    var jsonData = pm.response.json();
    pm.expect(jsonData.length).to.be.above(0);
});
➡️ Add test scripts to all requests.

📤 Step 5: Export Postman Collection
Click on Collection Name → 3 Dots → Export

Save as: postman_collection.json
